{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879911093,"sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab0f6b1001SNgtlAh1hrIHcx","messageID":"msg_d7ab0e7de001k2K6mXH9DN8kJK","sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879974701,"sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab10351001DAHd97fYzIe2yd","messageID":"msg_d7ab0e7de001k2K6mXH9DN8kJK","sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_69f937778b264d2f9ae1c812","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's code interpreter and agent runtime services. It consists of two primary client interfaces: `CodeInterpreterClient` for executing code and managing files in isolated sessions, and `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking agent workloads through the router.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py                 # Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n├── code_interpreter.py         # CodeInterpreterClient implementation\n├── agent_runtime.py            # AgentRuntimeClient implementation\n├── exceptions.py               # Exception hierarchy\n├── clients/\n│   ├── __init__.py             # Re-exports control plane and data plane clients\n│   ├── control_plane.py        # ControlPlaneClient for session management\n│   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n└── utils/\n    ├── __init__.py             # Module marker\n    ├── http.py                 # create_session utility\n    ├── utils.py                # read_token_from_file utility\n    └── log.py                  # get_logger utility\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐\n│   User Code     │─────▶│ CodeInterpreter  │─────▶│ Control Plane   │\n│                 │      │ Client           │      │ (Workload Mgr)  │\n└─────────────────┘      └────────┬─────────┘      └─────────────────┘\n                                  │\n                                  ▼\n                         ┌──────────────────┐\n                         │ Data Plane       │\n                         │ (Router)         │\n                         └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐\n│   User Code     │─────▶│ AgentRuntime     │─────▶│ Data Plane      │\n│                 │      │ Client           │      │ (Router)        │\n└─────────────────┘      └──────────────────┘      └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Public API\n\n### Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n### Client Classes Module (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n## CodeInterpreterClient\n\n### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Instance Attributes\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | Session name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | `int` | Session time-to-live in seconds |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Configured logger instance |\n| `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane client |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router URL for data plane |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier |\n| `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client |\n\n### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `_init_data_plane` | `() -> None` | Initialize data plane client |\n| `__enter__` | `() -> Self` | Enter context manager |\n| `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | Exit context manager, cleanup |\n| `stop` | `() -> None` | Stop session and cleanup resources |\n| `execute_command` | `(command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str` | Execute shell command |\n| `run_code` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str` | Run code in specified language |\n| `write_file` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Write content to file |\n| `upload_file` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Upload local file to remote |\n| `download_file` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | Download remote file locally |\n| `list_files` | `(path: str = \".\") -> Any` | List files in remote path |\n\n### Lifecycle Behavior\n\n#### Context Manager Cleanup\n\nWhen used as a context manager, `__exit__` calls `stop()` which:\n1. Closes the data-plane session\n2. Deletes the control-plane session (if `session_id` was set by the client)\n3. Closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Data Plane Init Failure\n\nIf `_init_data_plane()` raises after `create_session` succeeded:\n1. Log a warning\n2. Call `delete_session(session_id)`\n3. Set `session_id` to `None`\n4. Re-raise the exception\n\n#### Router URL Requirement\n\nIf neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set, raise `ValueError`.\n\n## AgentRuntimeClient\n\n### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Instance Attributes\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout in seconds |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Configured logger instance |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client |\n\n### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `__enter__` | `() -> Self` | Enter context manager |\n| `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | Exit context manager |\n| `invoke` | `(payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any` | Invoke agent with payload |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### Lifecycle Behavior\n\n#### Context Manager\n\nWhen used as a context manager, `__exit__` calls `close()` which closes the underlying `requests.Session`.\n\n#### Bootstrap Session ID\n\nIf `session_id` is not provided:\n1. Send GET to `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n2. Read response header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n3. If missing, raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n#### Invoke Without Session\n\nIf `session_id` is falsy when `invoke` is called, raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`.\n\n## ControlPlaneClient\n\n### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `create_session` | `(name: str, namespace: str, metadata: Optional[Dict] = None, ttl: int = 3600) -> str` | Create code interpreter session |\n| `delete_session` | `(session_id: str) -> bool` | Delete session by ID |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### HTTP Contract\n\n| Method | Path | Body |\n|--------|------|------|\n| `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` |\n| `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — |\n\n**Response Handling:**\n- `create_session`: Returns `data[\"sessionId\"]`. Raises `ValueError` if absent.\n- `delete_session`: Returns `True` on 404 (treated as success), otherwise logs and returns `False`.\n\n### Headers\n\n| Header | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |\n| `Authorization` | `Bearer {token}` if token is non-empty |\n\n### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Parameter | Source |\n|-----------|--------|\n| `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var |\n| `auth_token` | `auth_token` argument or contents of `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n\n### Timeout\n\n`(connect_timeout, timeout)` applied to each request.\n\n## CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `_request` | `(method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response` | Internal HTTP request |\n| `execute_command` | `(command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str` | Execute shell command |\n| `run_code` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str` | Run code |\n| `write_file` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Write file with base64 content |\n| `upload_file` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Upload file via multipart |\n| `download_file` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | Download file |\n| `list_files` | `(path: str = \".\") -> Any` | List files |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### Base URL Resolution\n\nIf `base_url` is not provided:\n```python\nbase_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n### HTTP Contract\n\n| Method | Relative Path | Body / Params |\n|--------|---------------|---------------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n\n**Headers:**\n- Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when body is set\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only\n\n**Note:** SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane; Router handles JWT.\n\n### Timeout Behavior\n\nFor `execute_command`, read timeout is `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit code 124.\n\n## AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n### Class Definition\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | Get session ID from GET request |\n| `invoke` | `(session_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> requests.Response` | Invoke agent |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### Base URL Resolution\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n### HTTP Contract\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | session default headers only | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n**Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` is method argument or `self.timeout` (default 120).\n\n## Utility Functions\n\n### create_session (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n```\n\nCreates a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for `http://` and `https://`.\n\n### read_token_from_file (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n```\n\nReturns file contents stripped, or empty string `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n\n### get_logger (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n```\n\nReturns a configured `logging.Logger` instance.\n\n## Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Handling Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Command returns non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` |\n| Session creation/management failure | `SessionError` (defined but not raised by core) |\n| Data plane operation failure | `DataPlaneError` (defined but not raised by core) |\n| Invalid configuration | `ValueError` |\n| HTTP errors | `requests` exceptions |\n\n## Configuration Summary\n\n### Default Values\n\n| Component | Parameter | Default |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | `timeout` | 120 |\n| ControlPlaneClient | `connect_timeout` | 5.0 |\n| ControlPlaneClient | `pool_connections` | 10 |\n| ControlPlaneClient | `pool_maxsize` | 10 |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `timeout` | 120 |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `connect_timeout` | 5.0 |\n| AgentRuntimeClient | `timeout` | 120 |\n| AgentRuntimeClient | `connect_timeout` | 5.0 |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `timeout` | 120 |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `connect_timeout` | 5.0 |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used By |\n|----------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **Client Initialization Tests**\n   - Test default parameter values\n   - Test environment variable resolution\n   - Test validation (e.g., required router_url)\n\n2. **Session Management Tests**\n   - Test `create_session` HTTP request/response\n   - Test `delete_session` with 404 handling\n   - Test context manager lifecycle\n\n3. **Data Plane Operations Tests**\n   - Test command execution with timeout\n   - Test file operations (write, upload, download, list)\n   - Test error handling (non-zero exit codes)\n\n4. **Exception Tests**\n   - Test `CommandExecutionError` raise conditions\n   - Test `ValueError` for invalid inputs\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **End-to-End Workflow**\n   - Create session → Execute code → Stop session\n   - Upload file → Run code → Download results\n\n2. **Agent Runtime Workflow**\n   - Bootstrap session → Invoke → Close\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n- Use `unittest.mock` for HTTP responses\n- Mock `requests.Session` and `requests.Response`\n- Test timeout behavior without actual network calls","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775879974688,"end":1775879974697}}}}
