{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879995045,"sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab23aef001XI2aaaJ19iAuV2","messageID":"msg_d7ab223ae0010DOKVb4YMuFNV1","sessionID":"ses_2854f29c5ffeHV9zCu3EQaKIE3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6eca4c85d3f242b893f3ca50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-021\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n5: - **Language**: Python\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: cmd/cli/\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\n20: ├── agentcube/\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\n22: │   ├── cli/\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\n25: │   ├── models/\n26: │   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n27: │   ├── runtime/\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n29: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\n30: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    # BuildRuntime\n31: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py                  # PublishRuntime\n32: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py                   # InvokeRuntime\n33: │   │   └── status_runtime.py                   # StatusRuntime\n34: │   ├── services/\n35: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Services package docstring\n36: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py                 # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n37: │   │   ├── docker_service.py                   # DockerService\n38: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py                     # KubernetesProvider\n39: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py               # AgentCubeProvider\n40: │   └── operations/\n41: │       └── __init__.py                         # Placeholder module docstring\n42: └── examples/\n43:     ├── hello-agent/\n44:     │   └── main.py                             # Example agent\n45:     └── math-agent/\n46:         └── main.py                             # Example agent\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### 1.3 Console Script Entry Point\n50: \n51: ```toml\n52: [project.scripts]\n53: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n54: ```\n55: \n56: The CLI is invoked as `kubectl-agentcube` with subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`.\n57: \n58: ## 2. Command Specifications\n59: \n60: ### 2.1 Global Options\n61: \n62: The root callback accepts:\n63: \n64: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n65: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n66: | `--version` | Optional[bool] | None | Show version and exit (eager option) |\n67: | `--verbose`, `-v` | bool | False | Enable verbose output |\n68: \n69: **Version Output**: `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` using Rich markup.\n70: \n71: **Verbose Behavior**: When `--verbose` is passed, `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` is called.\n72: \n73: ### 2.2 pack Command\n74: \n75: Validates and prepares a workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile.\n76: \n77: ```python\n78: def pack(\n79:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n80:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n81:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n82:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n83:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n84:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n85:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n86:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n87:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n88: ) -> None:\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Success Output**: Prints success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` using Rich `Progress` spinner.\n92: \n93: ### 2.3 build Command\n94: \n95: Builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local`.\n96: \n97: ```python\n98: def build(\n99:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n100:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 2871. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-021\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\n├── agentcube/","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775879995019,"end":1775879995041}}}}
